{{Infobox venue |stadium_name=Beijing University of Technology Gymnasium | image = Stadium of Beijing Institute of Technology.jpg |location=[[Beijing University of Technology]] |opened=2007 |owner=[[Beijing University of Technology]] | architect = [[South China University of Technology]] Institute of Architectural Design |tenants=[[Beijing University of Technology]] |seating_capacity=7,500}} The '''Beijing University of Technology Gymnasium''' ({{Zh|s=北京工业大学体育馆|t=北京工業大學體育館|p=Běijīng Gōngyè Dàxué Tǐyùguǎn}}) is an indoor arena located on the campus of the [[Beijing University of Technology]] in the [[Chaoyang District, Beijing|Chaoyang District]] in [[Beijing]], [[China]].
The gymnasium hosted the [[2008 Summer Olympics]] [[Badminton at the 2008 Summer Olympics|badminton]] and [[Gymnastics at the 2008 Summer Olympics|rhythmic gymnastics]] events.
The gymnasium seating capacity is 7,500 and has a floor space of 24,000 square metres.
After the Olympic Games, it has served as a training facility for Chinese badminton teams and also as a sports and recreational activities centre for students and local communities.
The gymnasium was completed in September 2007.
