{{Infobox football biography | name = Brandley Kuwas | image = | fullname = Brandley Kuwas | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1992|9|19|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Hoorn]], Netherlands | height = 1.78 m | position = [[Attacking midfielder]] | currentclub = [[Heracles Almelo]] | clubnumber = 17 | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = Hellas | youthyears2 = | youthclubs2 = [[AZ Alkmaar|AZ]] | youthyears3 = | youthclubs3 = KFC | years1 = 2012&ndash;2015 | clubs1 = [[FC Volendam]] | caps1 = 103 | goals1 = 15 | years2 = 2015&ndash;2016 | clubs2 = [[SBV Excelsior|Excelsior]] | caps2 = 34 | goals2 = 4 | years3 = 2016&ndash; | clubs3 = [[Heracles Almelo]] | caps3 = 66 | goals3 = 12 | nationalyears1 = 2017&ndash; | nationalteam1 = [[Curaçao national football team|Curaçao]] | nationalcaps1 = 2 | nationalgoals1 = 1 | club-update = 4 July 2018 | ntupdate = 10 September 2018 }}
'''Brandley Kuwas''' (born 19 September 1992) is a Curaçaoan professional [[association football|footballer]] who currently plays as an [[attacking midfielder]] for [[Heracles Almelo]] in the Dutch [[Eredivisie]] and the [[Curaçao national football team|Curaçao national team]].
==International career== Kuwas is of Curaçaoan descent, and played an unofficial match for the [[Curaçao national football team]] against Dutch club Excelsior in November 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vi.nl/nieuws/curacao-niet-langs-excelsior-bij-debuut-oranjetarget-kuwas-.htm|title=Cookies op VI.nl|website=www.vi.nl}}</ref> Kuwas made his international debut for Curaçao in a friendly 1–1 tie with [[El Salvador national football team|El Salvador]] on 22 March 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rtvoost.nl/pl.aspx?nid=265454|title=Assist Brandley Kuwas voor Curaçao tegen El Salvador|first=R. T. V.|last=Oost|date=23 March 2017|website=RTV Oost}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ad.nl/nederlands-voetbal/kuwas-debuteert-voor-nationale-ploeg-curaenccedil-ao~a0fe6d9c/|title=Cookies op AD.nl - AD.nl|website=www.ad.nl}}</ref>
