{{Infobox stadium | stadium_name = Eddy D. Field Stadium | nickname = | image = File:Eddy D. Field Stadium (Pepperdine).jpg | caption = | fullname = | location = [[Malibu, California]] | coordinates = {{coord|34.040272|-118.711042|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | capacity = 2,000 | broke_ground = | built = | opened = 1973 | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = | operator = | surface = | construction_cost = | architect = | structural engineer = | general_contractor = | former_names = | tenants = [[Pepperdine Waves baseball]] ([[National Collegiate Athletic Association|NCAA]]) | seating_capacity = | dimensions = }}
'''Eddy D. Field Stadium''' is home of the [[Pepperdine University]] [[Pepperdine Waves baseball|Waves' baseball team]] located in [[Malibu, California]]. It was originally built in 1973, but underwent renovations in 1980 and 1999. It now holds up to 2,000 spectators, all box seats. It is well known for its picturesque setting which includes the views of the [[Pacific Ocean]], [[Santa Catalina Island, California|Catalina Island]], and the [[Santa Monica Mountains]]. College baseball writer Eric Sorenson of [[CSTV]] ranked Eddy D. Field Stadium as the best college baseball stadium in Division I baseball.<ref>[http://www.cstv.com/sports/m-basebl/stories/050906adh.html Sorenson's Favorite Stadiums] at CSTV.com</ref>
