The '''Federação Cearense de Futebol''' ([[English language|English]]: Football Association of Ceará state) was founded on March 23, 1920, and it manages all the official [[association football|football]] tournaments within the state of [[Ceará]], which are the [[Campeonato Cearense]] and the [[Campeonato Cearense (lower levels)|Campeonato Cearense lower levels]], and represents the clubs at the [[Brazilian Football Confederation|Brazilian Football Confederation (CBF)]].

