'''Under Armour''' is an American [[sports clothing]] and accessories company. The company is a supplier of sportswear and casual apparel.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.bizjournals.com/baltimore/stories/2005/09/26/story6.html |title=Analysts: Brand crossover risky for Under Armour |work=[[Baltim. Bus. J.]] |date=September 26, 2005 |accessdate=May 1, 2015 |first=Robert J. |last=Terry }}</ref> [[Under Armour]] began offering footwear in 2006.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1336917/000119312509033942/d10k.htm |title=Form 10-K for the fiscal year ended December 31, 2008 |page=2 |date=February 20, 2009 |website=EDGAR |publisher=US SEC |accessdate=May 1, 2015 }}</ref> Its global headquarters is located in [[Baltimore|Baltimore, Maryland, US]], with additional North American corporate office locations in [[Austin, Texas|Austin]] and [[Houston|Houston, Texas]]; [[Denver|Denver, Colorado]]; [[New York City|New York, New York]]; [[San Francisco|San Francisco, California]]; [[Portland, Oregon]]; [[Nashville, Tennessee]]; and [[Toronto|Toronto, Ontario]]. Under Armour's International Headquarters is located in [[Panama City|Panama City, Panama]], with Latin America offices in [[São Paulo|São Paulo, Brazil]]; [[Santiago|Santiago, Chile]]; and [[Mexico City|Mexico City, Mexico]]. Its European headquarters is in Amsterdam's [[Olympic Stadium (Amsterdam)|Olympic Stadium]] with an additional office in [[Munich|Munich, Germany]].<ref>{{cite web|title = Under Armour Announces Multi-Year Partnership with FC St. Pauli and Opening of New Munich Office (NYSE:UA)|url = http://investor.underarmour.com/releasedetail.cfm?ReleaseID=923591|website = investor.underarmour.com|access-date = 2016-01-19}}</ref> The Under Armour [[Shanghai]] office is the regional headquarters for Greater China. Additional Asia Pacific offices are in [[Guangzhou|Guangzhou, China]]; [[Hong Kong]]; [[Jakarta|Jakarta, Indonesia]]; [[Tokyo|Tokyo, Japan]]; and [[Sydney|Sydney, Australia]].<ref>{{cite web |title = Under Armour Fact Sheet|url = http://underarmour.site.findly.com/locations/global-locations/|format = PDF|publisher = Under Armour|via = shareholder.com (NASDAQ OMX Group)|date = January 18, 2015}}</ref>
Under Armour promotes its products by sponsorship agreements with the following celebrity athletes, professional teams and college athletic teams, a field in which it competes with other sports apparel companies.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/05/25/sports/ucla-under-armour-sponsorship.html?_r=0|title=U.C.L.A. and Under Armour in Record Sponsorship Deal|newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|accessdate=2016-08-20}}</ref>
