{{about|the Palestinian footballer|the Canadian imam|Mohamed Elmasry}} <!--"Mohammed Al-Masry" redirects there"--> {{Infobox football biography | name = Mohammed Al-Masri | image = | height = {{height|m=1.85}} | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1981|10|08}} | birth_place =[[Jordan]] | currentclub = [[Shabab Al-Dhahrieh]] | clubnumber = 13 | youthyears1 = 1993–98 | youthclubs1 = [[Al-Yarmouk FC]] | position = [[Defender (association football)|Central Defender]] | years1 = 1998–2009 | years2 = 2009–10 | years3 = 2010– | clubs1 = [[Al-Yarmouk FC]] | clubs2 = [[Shabab Al-Ebadiyeh]] | clubs3 = [[Shabab Al-Dhahrieh]] | nationalyears1 = 2011– | nationalteam1 = [[Palestine national football team|Palestine]] | nationalcaps1 = 5 | nationalgoals1 = 0 }} '''Mohammed Al-Masri''' ({{lang-ar|محمد المصري}}; born October 8, 1981) is a [[Palestinian people|Palestinian]] center back who plays his club football for [[Shabab Al-Dhahrieh]].<ref>{{cite news | title=نجوم استفتاء "أيام الملاعب" يتحدثون | date=2011-11-02 | url=http://www.al-ayyam.com/article.aspx?did=156641&date=1/2/2011}}</ref> He was first called up to the national team for Palestine's [[2012 AFC Challenge Cup]] qualifying campaign,<ref>{{cite news | title= Palestine vs. Bangladesh Match Report | date=2011-03-21 | url=http://www.the-afc.com/en/component/joomleague/?view=report&compID=408&matchId=3638}}</ref> he received his first cap against Iran on October 5, 2011. Al-Masri has since gone on to represent Palestine at the [[2011 Pan Arab Games]].<ref>{{cite news | title= Palestine Team Members| date=2011-12-19 | url=http://rs.arabgames2011.qa/ENG/FB/FBE133A_FBM400400@@@@@@@@ENG_number=307.htm}}</ref>
