The '''Russian Chess Federation''' ({{Lang-ru|Российская Шахматная Федерация|translit=Rossiyskaya Shakhmatnaya Federatsiya}}) is the governing body for [[chess]] in [[Russia]] and the officially recognized arm of the [[Fédération Internationale des Échecs|FIDE]] in Russia. It was founded on 15 February 1992,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ruchess.ru/en/federation/|title=Federation|website=Russian Chess Federation|access-date=2017-08-07}}</ref> following the dissolution of the [[USSR Chess Federation]]. Its headquarters are in [[Moscow]]. The current president is [[Andrey Filatov]], who was elected in 2014.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.chessdom.com/andrey-filatov-elected-president-of-russian-chess-federation/|title=Andrey Filatov elected President of Russian Chess Federation|last=Kublashvili|first=Eteri|date=2014-02-03|website=Chessdom|access-date=2017-08-07}}</ref> The structure of the Russian Chess Federation consists of three governing bodies: the Congress, the supervisory board and the board of management.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.chessvibes.com/filatov-elected-president-of-the-russian-chess-federation|title=Filatov Elected President of the Russian Chess Federation|last=|first=|date=2014-02-03|website=ChessVibes|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2017-08-07}}</ref>

On 25 September 2014, a chess museum opened in the Russian Chess Federation's mansion.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://ruchess.ru/en/rcf-chess-museum/|title=RCF Chess Museum|last=|first=|date=|work=Russian Chess Federation|access-date=2017-08-07|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://en.chessbase.com/post/museum-of-chess-inaugurated-in-moscow|title=Museum of Chess inaugurated in Moscow|date=2014-09-27|work=Chess News|access-date=2017-08-07|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.chess.com/news/view/russias-first-chess-museum-opened-in-moscow-8334|title=Russia's First Chess Museum Opens in Moscow|last=Doggers|first=Peter|date=2014-09-28|work=Chess.com|access-date=2017-08-07|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://chess-news.ru/en/node/16766|title=Chess History Exhibited Near Kremlin|last=|first=|date=2014-09-27|website=chess-news.ru|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2017-08-07}}</ref>

